[medium] src/views/control-implementations/IndexView.vue:501 (concurrency/races)
loadDashboardSuggestionState captures the SSP id at request start, but the shared useDataApi refs are still updated when that old request resolves. If the user switches SSPs while a dashboard-suggestion request for the previous SSP is in flight, the old response can overwrite pendingDashboardSuggestions/dashboardSuggestionControlResults after the new SSP has loaded; if it resolves last, the drawer can permanently show suggestions/results from the wrong SSP and loadedDashboardSuggestionStateFor is set to the stale id.
Suggested fix: Gate commits by a request token/current SSP check and avoid letting stale useDataApi responses write directly to the shared refs. For example, fetch these two endpoints into local arrays with axios (or another non-state-bound helper), then assign pendingDashboardSuggestions/dashboardSuggestionControlResults and loadedDashboardSuggestionStateFor only if the token is still current and systemStore.system.securityPlan?.uuid still equals the requested SSP.
Guidance: In src/views/control-implementations/IndexView.vue, fix loadDashboardSuggestionState so stale SSP requests cannot write into pendingDashboardSuggestions, dashboardSuggestionControlResults, or loadedDashboardSuggestionStateFor. The current fetchPendingDashboardSuggestions/fetchDashboardSuggestionControlResults functions come from useDataApi, whose watched ax.data updates the shared refs as soon as each response resolves, before loadDashboardSuggestionState can check the current SSP. Do not try to fix this only by checking before setting loadedDashboardSuggestionStateFor; the stale data refs will already have been overwritten. For these two dashboard-suggestion reads, use the existing axios = useAuthenticatedInstance() directly (or a local non-ref helper) and fetch into local variables: axios.get<DataResponse<DashboardSuggestion[]>>(buildDashboardSuggestionsEndpoint(sspId, 'pending'), { camelcaseStopPaths: [...] }) and axios.get<DataResponse<ControlSuggestionResult[]>>(buildDashboardSuggestionControlResultsEndpoint(sspId)). Keep Promise.allSettled so either request can fail independently. Add a monotonically increasing request token/ref such as dashboardSuggestionStateRequestId; increment it before starting a new load and also invalidate it when there is no SSP or the AI config is disabled. After both requests settle, commit local pending/control-results arrays and loadedDashboardSuggestionStateFor only if token still matches and systemStore.system.securityPlan?.uuid === sspId. On a rejected request, commit [] only for that request and only after the same freshness check; preserve the other successful local result. Keep the existing once-per-SSP in-flight behavior, but make sure a newer SSP load is allowed to start even while an older SSP load is still pending. Add an IndexView test with two SSP ids and deferred responses where the first SSP response resolves after the second; assert the rendered drawer/computed state keeps only the second SSP suggestions/results and loadedDashboardSuggestionStateFor is not reset to the first SSP.
