[medium] src/views/control-implementations/IndexView.vue:482 (correctness vs. the actual SDK/library)
The new pending-suggestions fetch relies on camelcaseStopPaths like data.proposedFilterLabelSet to preserve arbitrary label keys, but camelcase-keys stopPaths are exact paths over the original object shape. For the DataResponse array returned by /dashboard-suggestions, the nested label map path is under data.<index>.proposed_filter_label_set, so these stop paths never match. Real responses can still camelize label keys such as _policy or service_name into policy/serviceName, causing the drawer to show internal labels and display mutated label keys even though formatVisibleLabelSet expects the raw keys.
Suggested fix: Add array-aware stop-path handling in the axios camelcase interceptor (with tests covering DataResponse arrays), or fetch/transform dashboard suggestions so only the envelope and suggestion field names are camelized while label-set maps are assigned unchanged before rendering.
Guidance: Fix the camelcase stop paths for dashboard suggestion label maps. In src/views/control-implementations/IndexView.vue loadDashboardSuggestionState, the stop paths passed to the pending suggestions request currently use camel-cased keys: data.labelSet, data.proposedFilterLabelSet, data.originalProposedFilterLabelSet. camelcase-keys evaluates stopPaths against the original response key names, so these do not protect label maps from key conversion. Replace them with the original snake-case response paths: data.label_set, data.proposed_filter_label_set, and data.original_proposed_filter_label_set. Apply the same correction in src/composables/useDashboardSuggestions.ts refreshPendingSuggestions, which uses the same wrong stop paths for the main SuggestionsView flow. Do not use indexed paths such as data.0.proposed_filter_label_set; camelcase-keys matches array children with data.proposed_filter_label_set. Add a focused test for src/composables/axios/index.ts response conversion (or an existing composable test if easier) using a DataResponse array with proposed_filter_label_set: { _policy: 'x', service_name: 'api' } and assert the field name becomes proposedFilterLabelSet while the nested label keys remain exactly _policy and service_name. Also update any expectations that currently assert data.proposedFilterLabelSet in IndexView tests to assert data.proposed_filter_label_set instead.
